CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1952, pg. 26 reads: "Out to Repeat - Joe Louis, Eoline Thornton and Ted Rhodes, left to right, will be out to retain championships in their respective divisions in the twenty-sixth annual United Golfers Association Championships which gets under way at South Park (shown above) Monday. Louis and Thornton are the defending champions in the men's and women's amateur division.  Rhodes won the professional title last year. - South Park Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Several men putting on South Park golf course with fairway and trees in background
